3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an unsupervised learning framework for depth and feature representation learning, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel framework for visual odometry, which is an important task in artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper presents a new method for depth and feature representation learning, which are key topics in computer vision and pattern recognition.
